The paper discusses the construction and optimization of business process models, which falls under the domain of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also presents a visualization tool to aid in the process of process modeling, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of process models also involves data management and storage (cs.DB) and potentially artificial intelligence techniques for optimization (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the practical applications of the visualization tool, which could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
